King William s Town businessman Mbulelo Sabisa was sentenced to nine years in prison by the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Port Elizabeth last week. Sabisa was found guilty of fraud and contravention of the Income Tax Act and the VAT Act.Between November 1 2006 and January 31 2007, Sabisa submitted false income tax returns to the South African Revenue Service (SARS) in East London amounting to R500 000.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions